---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Cambodia Investor Visa & Residency Guide 2025";
const description = "Complete guide to Cambodia's investor visa and residency options. Affordable entry from $100,000, renewable long-stay visas, dollar-based economy, and path to citizenship after 7 years.";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": title,
  "description": description,
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Compare Expat Plans"
  },
  "datePublished": "2025-01-15",
  "dateModified": "2025-01-15"
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />

  <PageShell
    title={title}
    subtitle="Your complete guide to investor residency in Cambodia"
    heroImage="/images/countries/cambodia-hero-bg.png"
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-4">Cambodia Investor Visa: Quick Facts</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div>
          <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-700">Minimum Investment:</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-900"> $100,000+ (company/QIP)</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-700">Residency Duration:</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-900"> 1-year renewable (E-class visa)</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-700">Processing Time:</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-900"> 2-8 weeks (varies by route)</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-700">Path to Citizenship:</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-900"> Possible after 7 years residence</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-700">Healthcare Quality:</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-900"> Limited—Bangkok evacuation essential</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-700">Insurance Requirement:</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-900"> Strongly recommended (not mandatory)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview Section -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Cambodia offers one of Southeast Asia's most accessible investor residency pathways with
        relatively low investment thresholds and a dollar-based economy that eliminates currency
        risk. The Kingdom welcomes foreign investment through multiple visa categories, from
        simple business visas to Qualified Investment Project (QIP) schemes with significant benefits.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Investment options start around $100,000 for company formation or QIP participation, with
        the E-class (business) visa providing renewable long-term residency. Cambodia's relaxed
        approach to foreign ownership (except land), growing economy, and strategic position between
        Thailand and Vietnam make it attractive for entrepreneurs and investors seeking an
        uncomplicated Southeast Asian base.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Healthcare is Cambodia's main weakness—facilities in Phnom Penh and Siem Reap are improving
        but remain limited for serious conditions. Bangkok (1 hour flight) is the primary evacuation
        destination for anything beyond routine care. International health insurance with evacuation
        coverage is absolutely essential for life in Cambodia.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="decision-guide" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-800 mb-3">Cambodia Investor Visa is Ideal If You:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-900">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Want a dollar-based economy (no currency risk)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Seek low cost of living and doing business</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Prefer minimal bureaucracy and easy renewals</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Comfortable flying to Bangkok for healthcare</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Interested in eventual citizenship (7 years)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-800 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If You:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-900">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Need quality local healthcare for chronic conditions</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Want to own land directly (not possible for foreigners)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Prefer established regulatory frameworks</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Need strong second passport (Cambodia ranks ~93)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Want predictable, transparent legal system</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Box -->
    <CTABox variant="highlight">
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Planning your Cambodia investment?</strong> Get international health insurance with
        Bangkok evacuation coverage—essential for life in Cambodia.
      </p>
      <a href="/insurance-for/expats" class="inline-block bg-white text-primary-700 font-semibold px-6 py-2 rounded hover:bg-primary-50 transition" style="color: #1d4ed8 !important;">
        Compare Expat Insurance Plans
      </a>
    </CTABox>

    <!-- Official Requirements Section -->
    <section id="requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Investment Routes</h3>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Route 1: E-Class Business Visa + Company</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Register a Cambodian company with $100,000+ paid-up capital. E-class visa renewable
              annually, allows unlimited stay and work authorization. Simplest route for most investors.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Route 2: Qualified Investment Project (QIP)</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Register with Council for Development of Cambodia (CDC). Minimum $500,000 investment
              in approved sectors. Significant tax incentives: up to 9-year tax holiday,
              import duty exemptions.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Route 3: Special Economic Zone Investment</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Invest in Cambodia's Special Economic Zones. Additional incentives available.
              Manufacturing and export-focused businesses preferred.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Route 4: Real Estate (Long-Stay)</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Purchase condo (2nd floor+) with foreign ownership allowed. No direct visa pathway,
              but supports E-class business visa renewal. Can own buildings, not land directly.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">E-Class Visa Requirements</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Initial entry:</strong> E-visa or visa on arrival ($35-36)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Extension:</strong> Convert to EB (business) class at Immigration</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Work permit:</strong> Required if employed; investors often self-employed</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Annual renewal:</strong> Extensions granted with active business/investment</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Multiple entry:</strong> Available, allows unlimited re-entry during validity</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Required Documents</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span>Valid passport (6+ months validity, blank pages)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span>Passport-sized photos (4x6cm, white background)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span>Company registration certificate (for business visa)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span>Tax registration (patent tax paid)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span>Employment contract or directorship letter</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span>Proof of investment funds (bank statements)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span>Business plan (for QIP applications)</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements Section -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-800 mb-2">Insurance Status: Absolutely Essential</h3>
        <p class="text-red-900">
          While Cambodia doesn't mandate health insurance for investors, comprehensive international
          coverage with regional evacuation is non-negotiable. Local healthcare cannot handle
          serious conditions—Bangkok hospitals (1 hour flight) are the standard evacuation destination.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Minimum Recommended Coverage</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Minimum coverage:</strong> $500,000+ (serious conditions require Bangkok transfer)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Medical evacuation:</strong> Essential—minimum $100,000 for air ambulance to Bangkok</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Must include Thailand (Bangkok hospitals primary care destination)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Direct billing:</strong> Important for Bangkok hospitals (Bumrungrad, Bangkok Hospital)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>24/7 assistance:</strong> Required for coordination of cross-border evacuations</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Repatriation:</strong> Coverage to return home for extended treatment if needed</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Insurance Providers -->
    <section id="insurance-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
        For Cambodia, prioritize insurers with strong Southeast Asian networks and proven evacuation
        capabilities. Bangkok hospital direct billing is particularly valuable.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "Coverage", "Monthly Cost", "Key Feature"]}
        rows={[
          ["Cigna Global", "Comprehensive coverage", "$1M-$2M+", "$350-650+", "Excellent Asia network"],
          ["BUPA Global", "Premium care", "$1M+", "$400-750+", "Direct billing Bumrungrad"],
          ["Allianz Care", "Families", "$500K-$2M", "$300-550+", "Multi-country coverage"],
          ["Pacific Prime", "Asia specialists", "$500K-$1M", "$250-500", "Cambodia expertise"],
          ["SafetyWing", "Budget nomads", "$250K", "$80-150", "Affordable with evacuation"]
        ]}
      />

      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-4">
        *Costs vary by age, coverage level, and deductible. Prices shown are estimates for individuals aged 35-45.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Box -->
    <CTABox>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Need insurance with Bangkok evacuation coverage?</strong> Compare international plans
        with strong Southeast Asian networks.
      </p>
      <a href="/best/expat-health-insurance" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-2 rounded hover:bg-primary-700 transition" style="color: white !important;">
        Compare Insurance Plans
      </a>
    </CTABox>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown Section -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Visa & Company Setup Costs</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">E-visa / Visa on arrival</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$35-36</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">E-class 1-year extension</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$285-300</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Company registration</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$1,500-3,000</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Minimum paid-up capital</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$1,000+ (standard company)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Annual patent tax</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$300-500</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Legal/accounting setup</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$1,000-2,000</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center pt-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-900 font-semibold">First Year Total (Visa + Company)</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-primary-600">$4,000-8,000</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">QIP Investment Route</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Minimum investment</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$500,000</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">CDC registration fees</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$3,000-5,000</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Tax holiday benefit</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Up to 9 years</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Import duty exemptions</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Available for equipment</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Living Costs in Cambodia (Monthly)</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Rent (1BR Phnom Penh good area)</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$400-800</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Rent (serviced apartment)</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$800-1,500</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Utilities (electricity, water, internet)</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$100-200</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Groceries (Western style)</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$300-500</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Dining out</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$200-400</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-neutral-100 pb-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Health insurance</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">$200-500</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center pt-2">
            <span class="text-neutral-900 font-semibold">Comfortable Monthly Budget</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-primary-600">$1,500-3,000</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-semibold text-primary-600">Week 1</div>
          <div class="flex-grow bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Arrive & Initial Visa</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Arrive on tourist e-visa or visa on arrival ($35-36). Begin company
              formation process with local corporate service provider.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-semibold text-primary-600">Weeks 2-3</div>
          <div class="flex-grow bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Company Registration</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Register company with Ministry of Commerce. Obtain business license,
              tax registration, and patent tax certificate.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-semibold text-primary-600">Week 4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Extension</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Convert to E-class (business) visa extension. Submit company documents,
              employment/directorship proof. Pay extension fee.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-semibold text-primary-600">Week 5-6</div>
          <div class="flex-grow bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Process & Receive</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Immigration processes extension. Receive 1-year EB visa stamp in passport.
              Set up banking, office space if needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-semibold text-primary-600">Ongoing</div>
          <div class="flex-grow bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Annual Renewal</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mt-1">
              Renew E-class visa annually (~$285-300). Maintain active company status,
              pay patent tax. After 7 years continuous residence, citizenship may be possible.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Tech Entrepreneur in Phnom Penh</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-3">
            American startup founder registers software company with $5,000 initial capital.
            E-class visa approved. Operates business serving regional clients.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700">
            Outcome: Low overhead, dollar economy, easy banking. Uses Bangkok for any medical needs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Manufacturing Investor with QIP</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-3">
            Chinese investor establishes $800,000 garment factory through CDC QIP.
            Receives 6-year tax holiday and import duty exemptions on equipment.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700">
            Outcome: Significant tax savings, competitive labor costs, export market access.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Medical Emergency Evacuation</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-3">
            Investor suffers appendicitis in Siem Reap. Local hospital not equipped for
            laparoscopic surgery. Insurance arranges flight to Bangkok Hospital.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700">
            Outcome: Surgery in Bangkok same day, full recovery. Insurance covered $15,000 including transport.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Condo Owner Without Proper Visa</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-3">
            Australian retiree bought $150,000 condo assuming property = residency.
            No automatic visa from property ownership—needed to form company.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-amber-700">
            Outcome: Had to register shell company for E-class visa. Condo investment fine, but visa requires business.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Citizenship After 7 Years</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-3">
            French entrepreneur lived 7+ years in Cambodia with continuous E-class visa.
            Applied for naturalization, required Khmer language proficiency.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700">
            Outcome: Citizenship granted after 8 years total. Now holds both French and Cambodian passports.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Chronic Condition Management</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-3">
            Investor with Type 2 diabetes manages condition in Cambodia. Monthly Bangkok
            trips for endocrinologist check-ups and medication stock-up.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-amber-700">
            Outcome: Workable but requires planning. Local care insufficient for specialist needs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-1">1. Assuming Property = Residency</h3>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm">
            Buying a condo doesn't automatically grant residency rights. You still need
            a business visa (E-class) with a company or employment. Property supports
            your case but isn't sufficient alone.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-1">2. Skipping Health Insurance</h3>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm">
            Cambodia's healthcare cannot handle serious conditions. Without insurance,
            a medical emergency means paying $10,000-30,000+ out of pocket for evacuation
            and treatment in Bangkok. This is not optional.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-1">3. Trying to Buy Land Directly</h3>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm">
            Foreigners cannot own land in Cambodia. Only condos (2nd floor and above)
            or buildings on land. Land must be held through Cambodian nominee or
            long-term lease—both carry risks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-1">4. Neglecting Company Compliance</h3>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm">
            E-class visa depends on active company status. Failing to file taxes, pay
            patent tax, or maintain proper records can jeopardize visa renewal.
            Use a local accountant to stay compliant.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-1">5. Overestimating Legal Protections</h3>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm">
            Cambodia's legal system is developing. Contract enforcement can be
            unpredictable. Choose business partners carefully, conduct thorough
            due diligence, and don't invest more than you can afford to lose.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare System Access -->
    <section id="healthcare" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare Reality in Cambodia</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
          Cambodia's healthcare system has improved significantly but remains limited for serious
          conditions. International-standard clinics exist in Phnom Penh and Siem Reap for basic
          care, but complex procedures, surgery, and specialized treatment require evacuation
          to Bangkok, Singapore, or home country.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-4">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's Available Locally</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <li>• Basic primary care and check-ups</li>
              <li>• Minor injuries and illnesses</li>
              <li>• Routine dental care</li>
              <li>• Basic diagnostics (blood tests, X-rays)</li>
              <li>• Pharmacy/medications (most available)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Requires Bangkok Evacuation</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <li>• Any surgery beyond minor procedures</li>
              <li>• Cardiac emergencies</li>
              <li>• Cancer diagnosis and treatment</li>
              <li>• Serious accidents/trauma</li>
              <li>• Specialist consultations</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Best Healthcare Options in Cambodia</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Royal Phnom Penh Hospital:</strong> Best local option, some international standards, limited specialties</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Sen Sok International University Hospital:</strong> Modern facility, Korean management, improving standards</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>International SOS Clinic (Phnom Penh):</strong> Expatriate clinic, good for primary care, coordinates evacuations</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Raffles Medical (Phnom Penh):</strong> Singapore-based clinic, international standards for basic care</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold">•</span>
            <span><strong>Royal Angkor International Hospital (Siem Reap):</strong> Best option near Angkor Wat area</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-blue-900 text-sm">
          <strong>Essential Evacuation Planning:</strong> Bangkok is 1 hour by flight from Phnom Penh.
          Bumrungrad International Hospital and Bangkok Hospital are the primary evacuation destinations.
          Ensure your insurance has direct billing arrangements and 24/7 evacuation coordination.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQs Section -->
    <section id="faqs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I open a bank account in Cambodia?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Yes, with a valid visa and passport. USD accounts are common—Cambodia operates
            largely on US dollars. Some banks require an E-class visa; others accept
            tourist visas. ABA Bank, ACLEDA, and Canadia Bank serve foreigners well.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does the dollar economy work?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Cambodia uses both USD and Cambodian Riel (KHR). Most transactions over $1-2
            are in dollars. ATMs dispense USD. Change under $1 is given in Riel (4,000 KHR = $1).
            This eliminates currency risk for dollar-based investors.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I get Cambodian citizenship?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Yes, after 7 years of continuous legal residence. Requirements include Khmer
            language proficiency and cultural knowledge. Naturalization is discretionary
            but achievable. Dual citizenship is allowed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What business can foreigners operate?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Most businesses are open to 100% foreign ownership. Restricted sectors include
            land ownership, some retail, and tobacco. No minimum local shareholding required
            for most industries unlike some neighboring countries.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Cambodia safe for investors?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Generally yes—political stability has improved, violent crime affecting foreigners
            is rare. Main risks are property disputes, contract enforcement uncertainty,
            and petty crime in cities. Use reputable lawyers and due diligence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How are taxes for investors?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Corporate tax is 20% (standard), with QIP investors potentially receiving 3-9 year
            tax holidays. Personal income tax is progressive to 20%. No capital gains tax on
            property held 1+ year. Tax treaties with limited countries.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Final Verdict -->
    <section id="verdict" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Final Verdict</h2>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
          Cambodia offers one of Southeast Asia's most accessible investor residency pathways with
          genuinely low barriers to entry. The combination of a dollar-based economy, minimal
          bureaucracy, full foreign ownership of most businesses, and affordable living makes it
          attractive for entrepreneurs and investors willing to accept its limitations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
          Healthcare is the critical weakness—comprehensive international insurance with Bangkok
          evacuation coverage is absolutely non-negotiable. Local facilities handle basic needs
          but anything serious requires a 1-hour flight to Thai hospitals. Factor this reality
          into your planning and budget.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
          This is ideal for: entrepreneurs wanting low overhead, investors seeking emerging market
          exposure, remote workers attracted to affordability, or those building regional businesses.
          It's not ideal for retirees with health concerns, families prioritizing education quality,
          or those uncomfortable with developing-world infrastructure and governance.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href="/insurance-for/expats" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded hover:bg-primary-700 transition text-center" style="color: white !important;">
            Compare Expat Insurance Plans
          </a>
          <a href="/visas/investor-visa" class="inline-block bg-white border border-primary-600 text-primary-600 font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded hover:bg-primary-50 transition text-center">
            Explore Other Investor Visas
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

